nt et_module_setting et_lb_module_content\"><p>We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Support the Hope Center</p><ul><li>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</li><li>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</li><li>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</li></ul></div><div data-option_name=\"css_class\" class=\"css_class et_module_setting\"></div></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div>				<div data-placeholder=\"Button\" data-name=\"button\" class=\"et_module et_m_button ui-draggable ui-resizable et_first\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 100.45px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \"><span class=\"et_module_name\">Button<span class=\"et_module_width\"> (15%)</span></span><span class=\"et_move\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_delete\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_settings_arrow\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><div class=\"et_module_settings\"><div data-option_name=\"color\" class=\"color et_module_setting\">yellow</div><div data-option_name=\"size\" class=\"size et_module_setting\">small</div><div data-option_name=\"url\" class=\"url et_module_setting\">http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/</div><div data-option_name=\"window\" class=\"window et_module_setting\">off</div><div data-option_name=\"text\" class=\"text et_module_setting et_lb_module_content\">Monthly Donation</div><div data-option_name=\"align\" class=\"align et_module_setting\">left</div><div data-option_name=\"css_class\" class=\"css_class et_module_setting\"></div></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div><div data-placeholder=\"Button\" data-name=\"button\" class=\"et_module et_m_button ui-draggable ui-resizable\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 100.45px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \"><span class=\"et_module_name\">Button<span class=\"et_module_width\"> (15%)</span></span><span class=\"et_move\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_delete\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_settings_arrow\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><div class=\"et_module_settings\"><div data-option_name=\"color\" class=\"color et_module_setting\">yellow</div><div data-option_name=\"size\" class=\"size et_module_setting\">small</div><div data-option_name=\"url\" class=\"url et_module_setting\">http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation</div><div data-option_name=\"window\" class=\"window et_module_setting\">off</div><div data-option_name=\"text\" class=\"text et_module_setting et_lb_module_content\">One Time Donation</div><div data-option_name=\"align\" class=\"align et_module_setting\">center</div><div data-option_name=\"css_class\" class=\"css_class et_module_setting\"></div></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div><div data-placeholder=\"Button\" data-name=\"button\" class=\"et_module et_m_button ui-draggable ui-resizable\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 100.45px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \"><span class=\"et_module_name\">Button<span class=\"et_module_width\"> (15%)</span></span><span class=\"et_move\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_delete\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_settings_arrow\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><div class=\"et_module_settings\"></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div><div data-placeholder=\"Resizable Column\" data-name=\"resizable\" class=\"et_module et_m_column et_m_column_resizable ui-draggable ui-resizable ui-droppable ui-sortable et_m_column_no_modules\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 178.9px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \" aria-disabled=\"false\"><span class=\"et_module_name et_column_name\">Resizable Column<span class=\"et_module_width\"> (30%)</span></span> <span class=\"et_delete_column\"></span><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div><div data-placeholder=\"Logo\" data-name=\"logo\" class=\"et_module et_m_logo ui-draggable ui-resizable\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 79.96px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \"><span class=\"et_module_name\">Logo<span class=\"et_module_width\"> (12%)</span></span><span class=\"et_move\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_delete\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_settings_arrow\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><div class=\"et_module_settings\"><div data-option_name=\"logo_url\" class=\"logo_url et_module_setting et_lb_module_content\">http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Hope-Center-Logo-Dimensions-e1408731975790.png</div><div data-option_name=\"align\" class=\"align et_module_setting\">right</div><div data-option_name=\"css_class\" class=\"css_class et_module_setting\"></div></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div><div data-placeholder=\"Text Block\" data-name=\"text_block\" class=\"et_module et_m_text_block ui-draggable ui-resizable et_first\" style=\"height: auto !important; width: 681px; display: inline-block; z-index: 1; opacity: 1; \"><span class=\"et_module_name\">Text Block</span><span class=\"et_move\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_delete\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><span class=\"et_settings_arrow\" style=\"display: block; \"></span><div class=\"et_module_settings\"><div data-option_name=\"et_text_block_content\" class=\"et_text_block_content et_module_setting et_lb_module_content\"><p>Hayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area. Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled. Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown. But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.</p></div><div data-option_name=\"css_class\" class=\"css_class et_module_setting\"></div></div><div class=\"ui-resizable-handle ui-resizable-e\" style=\"z-index: 90; \"></div></div>\";s:16:\"layout_shortcode\";s:1741:\"[et_lb_text_block first_class=\"1\" css_class=\"\"]<p>We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Support the Hope Center</p><ul><li>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</li><li>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</li><li>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</li></ul>[/et_lb_text_block]\n[et_lb_button width=\"15\" first_class=\"1\" color=\"yellow\" size=\"small\" url=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\" window=\"off\" align=\"left\" css_class=\"\"]Monthly Donation[/et_lb_button]\n[et_lb_button width=\"15\" color=\"yellow\" size=\"small\" url=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation\" window=\"off\" align=\"center\" css_class=\"\"]One Time Donation[/et_lb_button]\n[et_lb_button width=\"15\"][/et_lb_button]\n[et_lb_resizable width=\"30\"]\n[/et_lb_resizable]\n[et_lb_logo width=\"12\" align=\"right\" css_class=\"\"]http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Hope-Center-Logo-Dimensions-e1408731975790.png[/et_lb_logo]\n[et_lb_text_block first_class=\"1\" css_class=\"\"]<p>Hayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area. Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled. Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown. But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.</p>[/et_lb_text_block]\n\";}'),('131', '11', '_et_disable_builder', '0'),('132', '139', '_edit_lock', '1413609268:2'),('133', '139', '_edit_last', '2'),('134', '139', '_et_disable_builder', '0');#endQuery
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `june_11_2013_posts`#endQuery
CREATE TABLE `june_11_2013_posts` (
  `ID` bigint(20) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `post_author` bigint(20) unsigned NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `post_date` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT '0000-00-00 00:00:00',
  `post_date_gmt` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT '0000-00-00 00:00:00',
  `post_content` longtext NOT NULL,
  `post_title` text NOT NULL,
  `post_excerpt` text NOT NULL,
  `post_status` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'publish',
  `comment_status` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open',
  `ping_status` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open',
  `post_password` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `post_name` varchar(200) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `to_ping` text NOT NULL,
  `pinged` text NOT NULL,
  `post_modified` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT '0000-00-00 00:00:00',
  `post_modified_gmt` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT '0000-00-00 00:00:00',
  `post_content_filtered` longtext NOT NULL,
  `post_parent` bigint(20) unsigned NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `guid` varchar(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `menu_order` int(11) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `post_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'post',
  `post_mime_type` varchar(100) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `comment_count` bigint(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  PRIMARY KEY (`ID`),
  KEY `post_name` (`post_name`),
  KEY `type_status_date` (`post_type`,`post_status`,`post_date`,`ID`),
  KEY `post_parent` (`post_parent`),
  KEY `post_author` (`post_author`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=144 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8#endQuery
INSERT INTO `june_11_2013_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES ('8', '1', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Emergency food and clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</li>\r\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Divine Appointment every Monday Night starting at 7pm (Worship, testimony, scripture and prayer)</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome', '', '', '2014-10-16 20:04:17', '2014-10-16 20:04:17', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=8', '0', 'page', '', '0'),('10', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '<h3>Our organization depends almost entirely on the grace of volunteers. Find ways to give hope to the hopeless.</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nVolunteer for\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Operation Hope</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Work training partnerships</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Special events</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<p>Fill out the form below to get more information about how you can serve. Thank you for your generosity!\r\n[contact_form]\r\n\r\nYou may also call the Hope Center at 530.538.8398 to discuss service opportunities.\r\n</div>', 'Serve', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'serve', '', '', '2013-06-12 15:18:12', '2013-06-12 15:18:12', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=10', '0', 'page', '', '0'),('11', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', 'We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</li>\r\n	<li>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</li>\r\n	<li>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><a href=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-118 size-full\" src=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/monthly-button.jpg\" alt=\"Donate Monthly\" width=\"107\" height=\"48\" /></a>                        <input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" /></form><img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\r\n\r\nHayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area. Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled. Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown. But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-72\" src=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Hope-Center-Logo-Dimensions-e1408731975790.png\" alt=\"Hope Center Logo \" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" />', 'Give', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'give', '', '', '2014-10-18 05:38:33', '2014-10-18 05:38:33', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=11', '0', 'page', '', '0'),('12', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', ' ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '12', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=12', '3', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0'),('13', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', ' ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '13', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=13', '2', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0'),('14', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', '2013-06-11 19:48:59', ' ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '14', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '2013-06-11 19:56:48', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=14', '1', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0'),('15', '1', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '', 'Learn', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '2013-06-11 19:47:11', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('16', '1', '2013-06-11 20:28:06', '2013-06-11 20:28:06', '', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 20:28:06', '2013-06-11 20:28:06', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('17', '1', '2013-06-11 20:28:55', '2013-06-11 20:28:55', '', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 20:28:55', '2013-06-11 20:28:55', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('18', '2', '2014-10-16 20:03:34', '2014-10-16 20:03:34', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\nWe offer\n<ul>\n	<li>Emergency food and clothing</li>\n	<li>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</li>\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\n	<li>Divine Appointment every Monday Night starting at 7pm (Worship, testimony, scripture and prayer)</li>\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-10-16 20:03:34', '2014-10-16 20:03:34', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('19', '1', '2013-06-11 20:33:52', '2013-06-11 20:33:52', '<div class=\"intro-box group\">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.</h3>\r\n<a class=\"more\" href=\"#services\">Learn more\r\n&amp; get help ↓</a>\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"events\"><span class=\"subheading\">Upcoming Events</span>\r\n[google-calendar-events type=\"list\" max=\"10\"]</div>\r\n<div id=\"services\"><a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>A Simple Gesture</h3>\r\nWe drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to food banks around Oroville. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need? Click for more info and to sign up!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Operation Hope - Food Ministry</h3>\r\nThe Operation Hope team meets at 6 AM on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings to prepare and package a fresh hot breakfast for those who are hungry. The breakfast is then served at local parks in Downtown Oroville. In addition, a hot lunch is served on Fridays at The Hope Center. Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Clothing Assistance</h3>\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>3 bottoms</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>4 tops</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 jacket</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 coat in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 pajama set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 sheet set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 blanket in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOccasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Day Use Center</h3>\r\nAt The Hope Center, a wet-weather, drop-in, day-use center is currently under construction. We currently serve hot meals and fellowship with the needy and homeless in our main warehouse that has a makeshift dining area and houses our Community Kitchen Trailer. We offer laundry services to homeless only Tuesday through Friday from 10am to 1pm. Showers available Tuesday through Thursday 9am to 1pm, and 11am to 1pm on Fridays.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Life Skills Academy (LSA)</h3>\r\nLife Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, local government agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 20:33:52', '2013-06-11 20:33:52', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('20', '1', '2013-06-11 21:06:59', '2013-06-11 21:06:59', 'We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to the Hope Center Food Bank.  The food is then broken down into food boxes for families/individuals in our community. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need?  We believe that Oroville can take care of it\'s own!  Click for more info and to sign up', 'A Simple Gesture', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-simple-gesture', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:28:25', '2013-07-18 18:28:25', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=20', '0', 'services', '', '0'),('22', '2', '2013-07-18 18:27:39', '2013-07-18 18:27:39', 'We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to the Hope Center Food Bank.  The food is then broken down into food boxes for families/individuals in our community. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need?  We believe that Oroville can take care of it\'s own!  Click for more info and to sign up', 'A Simple Gesture', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-autosave', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:27:39', '2013-07-18 18:27:39', '', '20', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/20-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('23', '1', '2013-06-11 21:16:00', '2013-06-11 21:16:00', 'The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday through Friday from 10 am to 11:30 am.  On Saturday mornings the Christian Faith Center Team feeds a Hot Meal from 9:30 am to 11 am.  On Sunday The Fathers House and the Op Hope Team join together and provide Sunday Supper Service from 4 pm to  5:30 pm.  Everyone is welcome.  Meals are served at The Hope Center, 1950 Kitrick Ave.', 'Operation Hope - Food Ministry', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'operation-hope-food-ministry', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:02:42', '2013-07-18 18:02:42', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=23', '0', 'services', '', '0'),('25', '1', '2013-06-11 21:16:52', '2013-06-11 21:16:52', 'Our warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 bottoms</li>\r\n	<li>4 tops</li>\r\n	<li>1 jacket</li>\r\n	<li>1 coat in a 6 month period</li>\r\n	<li>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li>1 pajama set</li>\r\n	<li>1 sheet set</li>\r\n	<li>1 blanket in a 6 month period</li>\r\n	<li>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOccasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month.', 'Clothing Assistance', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'clothing-assistance', '', '', '2013-06-11 21:16:52', '2013-06-11 21:16:52', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=25', '0', 'services', '', '0'),('27', '1', '2013-06-11 21:17:37', '2013-06-11 21:17:37', 'At The Hope Center, people can come in and sit-down to get out of the weather enjoy a cool drink of water or a hot cup of coffee.  If they like they can shoot some pool during the day. It is our desire to provide a safe place for people to be.  Hours of operation are 10-3pm Tuesday through Friday.', 'Day Use Center', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'day-use-center', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:24:19', '2013-07-18 18:24:19', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=27', '0', 'services', '', '0'),('29', '1', '2013-06-11 20:56:31', '2013-06-11 20:56:31', '<div class=\"intro-box group\">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.</h3>\r\n<a class=\"more\" href=\"#services\">Learn more\r\n&amp; get help ↓</a>\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"events\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.17em;\">A Simple Gesture</span></div>\r\n<div id=\"services\">\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n\r\nWe drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to food banks around Oroville. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need? Click for more info and to sign up!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Operation Hope - Food Ministry</h3>\r\nThe Operation Hope team meets at 6 AM on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings to prepare and package a fresh hot breakfast for those who are hungry. The breakfast is then served at local parks in Downtown Oroville. In addition, a hot lunch is served on Fridays at The Hope Center. Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Clothing Assistance</h3>\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>3 bottoms</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>4 tops</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 jacket</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 coat in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 pajama set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 sheet set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 blanket in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOccasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Day Use Center</h3>\r\nAt The Hope Center, a wet-weather, drop-in, day-use center is currently under construction. We currently serve hot meals and fellowship with the needy and homeless in our main warehouse that has a makeshift dining area and houses our Community Kitchen Trailer. We offer laundry services to homeless only Tuesday through Friday from 10am to 1pm. Showers available Tuesday through Thursday 9am to 1pm, and 11am to 1pm on Fridays.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Life Skills Academy (LSA)</h3>\r\nLife Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, local government agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 20:56:31', '2013-06-11 20:56:31', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('30', '1', '2013-06-11 21:18:27', '2013-06-11 21:18:27', 'Life Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, the ACADC Institute,  local agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.', 'Life Skills Academy (LSA)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'life-skills-academy-lsa', '', '', '2014-10-16 20:09:26', '2014-10-16 20:09:26', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=30', '0', 'services', '', '0'),('32', '1', '2013-06-11 21:18:02', '2013-06-11 21:18:02', '<div class=\"intro-box group\">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.</h3>\r\n<a class=\"more\" href=\"#services\">Learn more\r\n&amp; get help ↓</a>\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 21:18:02', '2013-06-11 21:18:02', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('33', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '', 'Serve', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '2013-06-11 19:48:00', '', '10', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/10-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('34', '1', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', '', 'Give', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', '2013-06-11 19:48:18', '', '11', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/11-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('36', '1', '2013-06-11 21:36:40', '2013-06-11 21:36:40', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class=\"more\" href=\"#services\">Learn more\r\n&amp; get help ↓</a>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 21:36:40', '2013-06-11 21:36:40', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-7/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('38', '1', '2013-06-11 21:51:35', '2013-06-11 21:51:35', '<h3>Our organization depends almost entirely on the grace of volunteers. Find ways to give hope to the hopeless.</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nVolunteer for\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Operation Hope</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Work training partnerships</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Special events</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<p>Fill out the form below to get more information about how you can serve. Thank you for your generosity!\r\n[contact-form 1 \"Contact form 1\"]\r\n\r\nYou may also call the Hope Center at 530.538.8398 to discuss service opportunities.\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Serve', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-2', '', '', '2013-06-11 21:51:35', '2013-06-11 21:51:35', '', '10', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/10-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('45', '2', '2013-07-18 18:02:25', '2013-07-18 18:02:25', 'The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday through Friday from 10 am to 11:30 am.  On Saturday mornings the Christian Faith Center Team feeds a Hot Meal from 9:30 am to 11 am.  On Sunday The Fathers House and the Op Hope Team join together and provide Sunday Supper Service from 4 pm to  5:30 pm.  Everyone is welcome.  Meals are served at The Hope Center, 1950 Kitrick Ave.', 'Operation Hope - Food Ministry', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '23-autosave', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:02:25', '2013-07-18 18:02:25', '', '23', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/23-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('46', '2', '2013-07-18 18:24:02', '2013-07-18 18:24:02', 'At The Hope Center, people can come in and sit-down to get out of the weather enjoy a cool drink of water or a cup of coffee.  If they like they can shoot some pool during the day. It is our desire to provide a safe place for people to be.  Hours of operation are 10-3pm Tuesday through Friday.', 'Day Use Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '27-autosave', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:24:02', '2013-07-18 18:24:02', '', '27', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/27-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('47', '1', '2013-06-11 22:12:41', '2013-06-11 22:12:41', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 22:12:41', '2013-06-11 22:12:41', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('48', '2', '2013-07-18 18:48:04', '2013-07-18 18:48:04', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Life Recovery Group (for Parolees returning to South Butte County)</li>\r\n	<li>Prayer Group every Wednesday Night starting at 7pm</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month (except for hot meals).  This weeks falls on the week of the second Thursday of the month.\r\n</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:48:04', '2013-07-18 18:48:04', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('51', '2', '2013-07-18 18:49:17', '2013-07-18 18:49:17', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Life Recovery Group (for Parolees returning to South Butte County)</li>\r\n	<li>Prayer Group every Wednesday Night starting at 7pm</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month (except for hot meals).  This weeks falls on the week of the second Thursday of the month.\r\n</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-18 18:49:17', '2013-07-18 18:49:17', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-10/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('53', '2', '2013-09-17 21:18:05', '2013-09-17 21:18:05', '<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Life Recovery Group (for Parolees returning to South Butte County)</li>\r\n	<li>Prayer Group every Wednesday Night starting at 7pm</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Red Rock Life Line Now Ministries Outreach</li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month (except for hot meals).  This weeks falls on the week of the second Thursday of the month.\r\n</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Welcome to the Hope Center', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-17 21:18:05', '2013-09-17 21:18:05', '', '8', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('55', '2', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', 'Beauty in Balance\r\nSometimes I struggle trying to walk out my faith in today’s world. It’s not easy to be an example of Jesus to others in today’s culture. As the Director of the Hope Center I get people pulling from all different directions but I want to talk about two areas. Social Action and Evangelical efforts. Many people and organizations want me to be more socially/politically engaged while others want me to be more hard-lined while sharing the gospel. It seems that I can never satiate both, but at times I can satisfy one or the other or so it seems. It gets really confusing and to tell the truth sometimes I just want to find a place to withdraw and wait out the storm. When I find myself in these storms I know I can look to Jesus for inspiration. As much as I like pleasing people; pleasing Him is all that really matters.\r\nJesus didn’t hide…he so loved the world that he entered it. I mean can you for one minute imagine the Son of God leaving heaven to come hang out with us? It seems crazy to me. I have a hard time wrapping my head around that one! If I call myself a follower of Jesus how can I turn from the world and try to escape it when he asks (and leads by example) for us to love it? I can’t. He called me to “love my neighbor” and that compels me to get involved in the issues and politics that affect our community. He also called me to make Disciples and that requires a strong Biblical Foundation and is an Evangelical mandate.\r\nIn an organizational sense this is accomplished by us here at the Hope Center by being very active in the social justice role (loving our neighbor) and being able to plug people in to existing church bodies in an effort to ensure they receive the biblical foundation necessary (evangelical). This is also a beautiful display of the Body of Christ at work. Those that are called to Social Action/Justice and those that are called to Teaching/Preaching!\r\nOn a personal level I totally want to engage in social action while embracing the creation mandate to love all of the creation (the secular world). God has a desire for all of creation (life) not just religious aspects of it. God loves it when His people get together and worship but he has a longing for those who don’t. So, I will continue to study scripture and be Biblically sound while taking on the issues of our community head on in hopes of making Jesus famous!\r\nMartin Luther King: “Religion deals with both heaven and earth…Any religion that professes to be concerned with the souls of men and is not concerned with the slums that doom them, the economic conditions that strangle them, and the social conditions that cripple them, is a dry-as-dust religion.”\r\nRecommend Read: “Balanced Christianity” by John Stott, Intervarsity Press\r\nIf you have a desire to partner with us please go to www.orovillehopecenter.org and hit the “Give” tab.\r\nBlessings', 'Beauty in Balance', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '55', '', '', '2014-07-16 23:09:31', '2014-07-16 23:09:31', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=55', '0', 'post', '', '0'),('59', '2', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', 'Beauty in Balance\r\nSometimes I struggle trying to walk out my faith in today’s world.  It’s not easy to be an example of Jesus to others in today’s culture.  As the Director of the Hope Center I get people pulling from all different directions but I want to talk about two areas.  Social Action and Evangelical efforts.  Many people and organizations want me to be more socially/politically engaged while others want me to be more hard-lined while sharing the gospel.  It seems that I can never satiate both, but at times I can satisfy one or the other or so it seems.  It gets really confusing and to tell the truth sometimes I just want to find a place to withdraw and wait out the storm.  When I find myself in these storms I know I can look to Jesus for inspiration.  As much as I like pleasing people; pleasing Him is all that really matters.  \r\nJesus didn’t hide…he so loved the world that he entered it.  I mean can you for one minute imagine the Son of God leaving heaven to come hang out with us?  It seems crazy to me.  I have a hard time wrapping my head around that one!  If I call myself a follower of Jesus how can I turn from the world and try to escape it when he asks (and leads by example) for us to love it?  I can’t.  He called me to “love my neighbor” and that compels me to get involved in the issues and politics that affect our community.  He also called me to make Disciples and that requires a strong Biblical Foundation and is an Evangelical mandate. \r\nIn an organizational sense this is accomplished by us here at the Hope Center by being very active in the social justice role (loving our neighbor) and being able to plug people in to existing church bodies in an effort to ensure they receive the biblical foundation necessary (evangelical).  This is also a beautiful display of the Body of Christ at work.  Those that are called to Social Action/Justice and those that are called to Teaching/Preaching!\r\nOn a personal level I totally want to engage in social action while embracing the creation mandate to love all of the creation (the secular world).  God has a desire for all of creation (life) not just religious aspects of it.  God loves it when His people get together and worship but he has a longing for those who don’t.  So, I will continue to study scripture and be Biblically sound while taking on the issues of our community head on in hopes of making Jesus famous!\r\nMartin Luther King:  “Religion deals with both heaven and earth…Any religion that professes to be concerned with the souls of men and is not concerned with the slums that doom them, the economic conditions that strangle them, and the social conditions that cripple them, is a dry-as-dust religion.”\r\nRecommend Read:  “Balanced Christianity” by John Stott, Intervarsity Press\r\nIf you have a desire to partner with us please go to www.orovillehopecenter.org and hit the “Give” tab.\r\nBlessings\r\n', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '55-revision', '', '', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', '2014-07-16 21:00:09', '', '55', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/55-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('61', '2', '2014-07-21 01:58:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '&lt;iframe src=\"http://www.google.com/calendar/embed?src=orovillehopecenter.org_7nmf5uv2brbpmig7v192nflu8k%40group.calendar.google.com&amp;ctz=America/Los_Angeles\" style=\"border: 0\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2014-07-21 01:58:07', '2014-07-21 01:58:07', '', '0', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?page_id=61', '0', 'page', '', '0'),('62', '2', '2014-07-21 01:57:56', '2014-07-21 01:57:56', '<iframe src=\"http://www.google.com/calendar/embed?src=orovillehopecenter.org_7nmf5uv2brbpmig7v192nflu8k%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=America/Los_Angeles\" style=\"border: 0\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '61-revision', '', '', '2014-07-21 01:57:56', '2014-07-21 01:57:56', '', '61', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/61-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('64', '1', '2013-06-11 21:54:34', '2013-06-11 21:54:34', '<h3>We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.</h3>\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"BEYXHT8VC9N3Y\" />\r\n<input type=\"image\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /></form>Hayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area. Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled. Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown. But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.\r\n\r\nThis is why we will be establishing a comprehensive fundraising plan, which begins with the formation of a fundraising team. This team will be comprised of people who will oversee, coordinate and implement fundraising strategies, such as special events, campaigns by mail, online, and through local media such as television and news publication. They will also search for grant opportunities and maintain current grant submissions and applications. This team will be intimately involved with all facets of Hayden Ministries in order to present a current picture of our status.', 'Give', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-06-11 21:54:34', '2013-06-11 21:54:34', '', '11', 'http://orovillehopecenter.org/11-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),('65', '2', '2014-08-22 00:25:25', '2014-08-22 00:25:25', '<h3>We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.</h3>\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"BEYXHT8VC9N3Y\" />\r\n<input type